name: Ayam Goreng Prambanan
address: Jl. Raya Kapal No.77, Kapal, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
One of the places in Bali that makes halal food with good service.
The ayam Bakar is not bad. I like the bumbu which they use and how they baste it. The vegetable portion is a little small and they didn't have basil leaves to go with the ayam bakar. The soda gembira was nice to drink at the end of the lunch. Overall it's still a nice place to eat.
review 2: Tasty central java style food with moderate to cheap price. Popular for local travellers because it's located at the major road just when people going out/in to the Denpasar.
review 3: Ok place for a quick lunch during trip to/from denpasar-gilimanuk. Good ayam kampung goreng,  yet the sambal is not really as per expectation.  The soto ayam kampung is superb!  The broth is clear but full of taste!

name: Warung Tegan
address: C5CM+9RF, Jl. Raya Kapal, Kapal, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
Tilapia (mujair) is fresh, seemingly they grow their own within the premise. And they make it easy for us to eat the fish (we had the fried ones) because they separated the meat from the body, it is served on top of the bones. I mean, thoughtful. It's not spicy like in general in Bali. The happy soda (Es Soda Gembira) is generous!

The place is clean and nice, plants are nicely arranged, by the paddy field, although it can be a bit noisy because it's by the main road. Service is okay, serving is quite fast, price is good. When it's busy, maybe parking can be a bit of a problem. They have yoga and meditation classes occasionally.
review 2: the gurame nyat nyat was delicious, we also had fried shrimp which is super good. the service is fast and the price is affordable too. I was enjoying the dish I took the picture halfway I eaten the dish
review 3: Nice grilled gurami fish, always visit this place to eat grilled gurami fish.
review 4: Great Place, Fresh Gurami. A littlet bit busy at dinner time
review 5: The best seafood restaurant in my town

name: Bhanana Bistro and Kids Club
address: Kapal, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: The place is great for kids & family. Not too crowded and very cheap (only IDR25.000 during weekend & IDR10.000 at weekdays) the food is good & they also have great selection of coffee & juice. Reccomended for rest area especially you're travelling to North of Bali with kids üëçüëçüëç
review 2:
nice place for your kids, located near Mangusada Hospital. I ordered aglio olio fettucine, french fries and garlic bread. Aglio Olio is too spicy for me, I love the garlic bread here.

plus thing is this place have kids club and we only pay once then our kids can play for whole day
review 3: Tuesday 1st may 2018, I'm here and it's a nice place for a casual atmosphere, hanging out with a menu of western menus, and I like my menu choices, sandwiches with fries, drinking capucino ice, love to be here.
review 4: ...A family resto with strategic location, cozy place, ambience atmosphere,  a lot of choices from light meals to heavy meals,  snack,  and other drinks,  but limited parking lot (roadside),  A perfect place to hang out with family,  friends or colleagues...
review 5:
Bad experience. We visited this place craving for Western food, but when we were ready to order it occurred that they don't have any salads, mashed potatoes, cream soups, beef steaks, so basically what they had was rice, chicken and french fries (you can get this on every corner in Bali). I ended up with spaghetti carbonara that they did have, and they brought me plain spaghetti with creamy sauce. When I asked where is ham they said there's no ham in their receipt of carbonara (greedy indonesian receipt I guess).

On the end of this we received a receipt with 10% of service charge, that wasn't mentioned in their menu. In my opinion asking extra money "for service" when you don't have 80% of the dishes from menu is absolutely rude.

I recommend this place only for perverts who want to eat chicken rice and pay  western price.
